    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-09-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="269"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Burlingame</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 34.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-09-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 2, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 18th of April (No. 36) has
                    been received and is approved.</p>
                <p>I have the pleasure of expressing the satisfaction of the government with the
                    just and liberal conduct of Sir Frederick Bruce, and the acquiescence of the
                    Russian and French ministers, in regard to the subject of concessions of land in
                    the treaty ports to foreign governments.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Anson Burlingame</hi>, Esq, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
